%N A394577 Number of almost irreducible meanders with n intersections.
%C A394577 An almost irreducible meander is an open meander obtained from a singular irreducible meander via insertion of a cup (open meander with two intersections) into each tangential intersection.
%H A394577 Yury Belousov, <a href="http://ftp.pdmi.ras.ru/pub/publicat/znsl/v549/p049.pdf">Singular meanders</a>, Zap. Nauchn. Sem. POMI, 549 (2025), 49-64.
%H A394577 Yury Belousov, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2112.10289">Prime Factorization of Meanders</a>, arXiv:2112.10289 [math.CO], 2025.
%H A394577 Yury Belousov, <a href="https://github.com/YuryBelousov/meander_factorization">C++ code for generating the sequence</a>, GitHub.
%F A394577 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} A393654(n-k,k).
